descriptions.fusion-power: Start producing electric power by fusion powerplant.

descriptions.golem: Survive a hit of 500 damage or more.
descriptions.it-stinks-and-they-do-like-it: Attract a group of pentapods using spores.

descriptions.shattered-planet-2: Travel 30 000 km towards the shattered planet.
descriptions.shattered-planet-3: Travel 60 000 km towards the shattered planet.

descriptions.research-with-logistics: Research a technology using logistic science packs.

descriptions.lazy-bastard: Launch a rocket to space while manually crafting no more than 111 items.
descriptions.steam-all-the-way: Launch a rocket to space without building any solar panels.
descriptions.raining-bullets: Launch a rocket to space without building any laser turrets.
descriptions.logistic-network-embargo: Finish research with space science pack for the base game or any planetary science pack for Space Age without building any active provider, buffer, or requester chests.
descriptions.no-time-for-chitchat: Launch a rocket to space within 15 hours.
descriptions.there-is-no-spoon: Launch a rocket to space within 8 hours.

descriptions.water: If disabled: only in starting area

descriptions.underground-belt: Used to allow a belt to cross entities or impassable terrain.
descriptions.fast-underground-belt: Used to allow a belt to cross entities or impassable terrain.
descriptions.express-underground-belt: Used to allow a belt to cross entities or impassable terrain.
descriptions.turbo-underground-belt: Used to allow a belt to cross entities or impassable terrain.
descriptions.splitter: Splits and/or joins transport belts' cargo 1:1.
descriptions.fast-splitter: Splits and/or joins transport belts' cargo 1:1.
descriptions.express-splitter: Splits and/or joins transport belts' cargo 1:1.
descriptions.turbo-splitter: Splits and/or joins transport belts' cargo 1:1.
descriptions.stack-inserter: Stack inserter capable of filling transport belts in layers.
descriptions.rail-signal: Defines the rail system into blocks, allowing multiple trains to run on the same network.
descriptions.rail-chain-signal: Reads the next signals in the path to allow better control of the trains.
descriptions.locomotive: Runs automated schedules and pulls rolling stock.
descriptions.construction-robot: Automatically build and repair friendly entities.
descriptions.active-provider-chest: Sends its content to the logistic network.
descriptions.passive-provider-chest: Makes its content available to the logistic network.
descriptions.storage-chest: Long-term storage for the logistic network.
descriptions.buffer-chest: Requests specified items to be available for personal logistics and automated construction.
descriptions.requester-chest: Requests specified items from the logistic network.
descriptions.roboport: Connects with other roboports to create the construction and logistic networks used by construction and logistic robots.
descriptions.arithmetic-combinator: Performs arithmetic operations on circuit network signals.
descriptions.selector-combinator: Performs sorting operations on circuit network signals.
descriptions.power-switch: Used to control the connections of the electric network. Can also be controlled by the circuit network.
descriptions.programmable-speaker: Connects to the circuit network in order to play alarms and musical notes, or show alerts.
descriptions.boiler: Burns fuel to turn water into steam.
descriptions.steam-engine: Consumes steam to create electric energy.
descriptions.solar-panel: During daytime it produces 100% of the power output which drops to 0% at night.
descriptions.accumulator: Stores a limited amount of energy when available production exceeds demand, and releases it in the opposite case.
descriptions.nuclear-reactor: Uses uranium fuel cells to generate heat. The heat output increases when built next to other reactors.
descriptions.heat-exchanger: Uses heat energy to turn water into steam.
descriptions.steam-turbine: Consumes steam to create electric energy.
descriptions.fusion-reactor: Uses fluoroketone with fusion power cells to make plasma.
descriptions.fusion-generator: Consumes plasma to create electric energy.
descriptions.big-mining-drill: A larger more powerful drill with a large mining area. Can mine harder ores.
descriptions.offshore-pump: Extracts fluid from bodies of water, lava, and various oceans.
descriptions.foundry: Allows new smelting and metallurgy recipes.
descriptions.recycler: The recycler reverses most processes except smelting and chemistry, returning 25% of the ingredients on average. Fluid ingredients are not regained. Other items are usually returned 25% of the time (losing 75%), or turned to spoilage if they were biological.
descriptions.agricultural-tower: Plants seeds and harvests mature plants.
descriptions.captive-biter-spawner: This creature requires food and will slowly starve if not fed. It will transform upon starvation. It can be captured by targeting [entity=biter-spawner] with [item=capture-robot-rocket]
descriptions.electromagnetic-plant: Critical for electromagnetic research and processes.
descriptions.cryogenic-plant: Can handle extremely low temperatures. Critical for cryogenic research and processes.
descriptions.lightning-rod: Protects a small area from lightning strikes and converts the energy into the electric network.
descriptions.lightning-collector: Protects a large area from lightning strikes and converts the energy into the electric network.
descriptions.heating-tower: Generates heat from chemical fuels with very high efficiency. Does not stop burning when at maximum temperature. Passes heat to connected heat pipes which can be used for steam power, or to prevent freezing.
descriptions.beacon: Transmits the effect of modules to nearby friendly entities. Transmission effects stack with diminishing returns.
descriptions.rocket-silo: Used to launch items and players to space platforms.
descriptions.space-platform-hub: The platform hub is the core of the space platform. It receives items from planets and dispatches them to cargo landing pads. It is created by launching [item=space-platform-starter-pack].
descriptions.cargo-bay: Increases the hub and landing pad inventory size.
descriptions.asteroid-collector: Collects small asteroids. Large asteroids must be broken up into smaller chunks by turrets.
descriptions.crusher: Can crush certain items, such as asteroids, into smaller chunks.
descriptions.thruster: Allows space platforms to travel to other planets. Must be built on the south edge of space platform.
descriptions.radar: Scans the nearby sectors, and actively reveals an area around it.
descriptions.flamethrower-turret: Fires a stream of burning liquid at enemies.
descriptions.tesla-turret: Electrocutes a nearby enemy. The electric bolt can bounce to secondary enemies in an arcing chain.
descriptions.railgun-turret: A long range electric cannon turret. Effective against enemies and asteroids.
descriptions.yumako-tree: A Gleba tree that yields tasty nutritious yumako fruit.
descriptions.jellystem: A Gleba abomination with a jelly-like stem and soft fleshy lumps that grow wrinkled jellynuts.
descriptions.cargo-pod:
Used to transfer items from the space platform to the planet's surface.
It is launched automatically upon a space platform arriving in orbit if the [entity=cargo-landing-pad] is requesting cargo.
It can be sent manually by Unknown control sequence: "stack-transfer" on the item icon in the space platform hub GUI.
descriptions.cargo-pod-container:
Appears on the planet's surface with cargo from the space platform. It is destroyed upon removing the cargo.
When [entity=cargo-landing-pad] is built, delivery pods stop arriving at the initial coordinates, and cargo is delivered directly there.
descriptions.small-demolisher: A massive territorial creature with high regeneration. Does not like to be disturbed.
descriptions.medium-demolisher: A massive territorial creature with high regeneration. Does not like to be disturbed.
descriptions.big-demolisher: A massive territorial creature with high regeneration. Does not like to be disturbed.
descriptions.slipstack: A Gleba coral stack that excretes blobs of slippery mucus.
descriptions.funneltrunk: A Gleba fungus that forms a hard outer funnel and cultivates symbiotic worms.
descriptions.hairyclubnub: A Gleba fungus with hard woody stems and club-like caps that catch flies with sticky hairs.
descriptions.teflilly: A Gleba plant with strong plasticy leaves.
descriptions.lickmaw: A carnivorous Gleba abomination with tongue-like tentacles and many mouths.
descriptions.stingfrond: A Gleba lichen with a dry wispy canopy that lowers exceptionally strong cords armed with tiny stinging barbs.
descriptions.boompuff: A Gleba lichen with pressurised gas sacs that ferments decaying matter into explosive gasses.
descriptions.sunnycomb: A Gleba lichen with a sponge-like structure that accumulates a yellow crust when dried by the sun.
descriptions.cuttlepop: A Gleba fungus with tentacle-like roots and rattling spore pods.
descriptions.copper-stromatolite: A rocky formation caused by copper bacteria.
descriptions.iron-stromatolite: A rocky formation caused by iron bacteria.
descriptions.fulgoran-ruin-attractor: Protects a small area from lightning strikes.
descriptions.lightning: Lightning is a natural phenomenon that damages unprotected entities and the player character. At the same time, it can be used as a source of energy.
descriptions.parameter-0: Parameters are used for setting the generic blueprints in the blueprint configuration menu.
descriptions.parameter-1: Parameters are used for setting the generic blueprints in the blueprint configuration menu.
descriptions.parameter-2: Parameters are used for setting the generic blueprints in the blueprint configuration menu.
descriptions.parameter-3: Parameters are used for setting the generic blueprints in the blueprint configuration menu.
descriptions.parameter-4: Parameters are used for setting the generic blueprints in the blueprint configuration menu.
descriptions.parameter-5: Parameters are used for setting the generic blueprints in the blueprint configuration menu.
descriptions.parameter-6: Parameters are used for setting the generic blueprints in the blueprint configuration menu.
descriptions.parameter-7: Parameters are used for setting the generic blueprints in the blueprint configuration menu.
descriptions.parameter-8: Parameters are used for setting the generic blueprints in the blueprint configuration menu.
descriptions.parameter-9: Parameters are used for setting the generic blueprints in the blueprint configuration menu.
descriptions.capture-robot-rocket: Grapples on and captures the targeted [entity=biter-spawner] into [entity=captive-biter-spawner].
descriptions.crash-site-chest-1: A container from the crashed ship. It might contain useful items.
descriptions.crash-site-chest-2: A container from the crashed ship. It might contain useful items.
descriptions.entity-ghost: Building plan of an entity, more in [tip=ghost-building]
descriptions.entity-unknown: This entity is not available due to mod removal, it will be restored if the mod is re-enabled.
descriptions.item-on-ground:
Can be picked up by pressing Unknown control sequence: "pick-items".
Can be dropped manually [tip=z-dropping] or by entities like [entity=burner-mining-drill].
descriptions.item-request-proxy: This is to indicate a request for construction bots to deliver an item to this entity. Unknown control sequence: "mine" to delete the item request.
descriptions.capture-robot: Grapples on and captures the targeted [entity=biter-spawner] into [entity=captive-biter-spawner].

descriptions.fusion-plasma:
Ultra-high-temperature ions generated in [entity=fusion-reactor] and consumed by a [entity=fusion-generator]. It is not a normal fluid and cannot be moved in [entity=pipe], it can only be moved through the Fusion reactor and Fusion generator.
The temperature of plasma determines its energy value.
A quantity of plasma also represents that amount of coolant that travels with it, and the heated coolant is output by the Fusion generator as the plasma is used for energy.
descriptions.fluid-unknown: This fluid is not available due to mod removal, it will be restored if the mod is re-enabled.

descriptions.rail:
Use to build straight rails manually or through the rail planner.
Unknown control sequence: "build" to build short paths directly.
Unknown control sequence: "build-ghost" to place long ghost paths.
Unknown control sequence: "toggle-rail-layer" to switch between ground and elevated paths.
descriptions.landfill: Can be placed on water to create terrain you can build on.
descriptions.overgrowth-yumako-soil: Soil for [entity=yumako-tree] placeable anywhere in the green biome.
descriptions.overgrowth-jellynut-soil: Soil for [entity=jellystem] placeable anywhere in the red biome.
descriptions.ice-platform: A stable floating platform of ice for sufficiently cold planets. Will melt if exposed to heat unless protected by a layer of concrete or other heat resistant material.
descriptions.foundation: Engineered structural foundation with heat shielding and deep screw piles. Can be placed on lava, oil ocean, and most water.
descriptions.deconstruction-planner: Marks items for deconstruction by construction robots.
descriptions.upgrade-planner: Marks items for upgrade by construction robots.
descriptions.speed-module: Increases machine speed at a cost of increased energy consumption.
descriptions.speed-module-2: Increases machine speed at a cost of increased energy consumption.
descriptions.speed-module-3: Increases machine speed at a cost of increased energy consumption.
descriptions.efficiency-module: Decreases machine energy consumption. Minimum energy consumption is 20%.
descriptions.efficiency-module-2: Decreases machine energy consumption. Minimum energy consumption is 20%.
descriptions.efficiency-module-3: Decreases machine energy consumption. Minimum energy consumption is 20%.
descriptions.productivity-module:
Machine will create extra products at a cost of increased energy consumption and reduced speed.
Usable only on intermediate products.
descriptions.productivity-module-2:
Machine will create extra products at a cost of increased energy consumption and reduced speed.
Usable only on intermediate products.
descriptions.productivity-module-3:
Machine will create extra products at a cost of increased energy consumption and reduced speed.
Usable only on intermediate products.
descriptions.quality-module: Allows machine to make higher quality products.
descriptions.quality-module-2: Allows machine to make higher quality products.
descriptions.quality-module-3: Allows machine to make higher quality products.
descriptions.empty-module-slot: An empty module slot in a machine. Used in upgrade planners to install new modules or uninstall existing modules.
descriptions.yumako-seed: Can be planted on yumako soil.
descriptions.jellynut-seed: Can be planted on jellynut soil.
descriptions.yumako: Nutritious farmable crop. Grants burst of health regeneration when eaten.
descriptions.jellynut: Slimy farmable crop. Grants burst of movement speed when eaten.
descriptions.bioflux: Highly nutritious blend of Gleba crops. Grants burst of both health regeneration and movement speed when eaten.
descriptions.yumako-mash: Grants burst of health regeneration when eaten.
descriptions.jelly: Grants burst of movement speed when eaten.
descriptions.space-science-pack: Used by labs for research. Obtained by processing asteroids in space.
descriptions.space-platform-foundation: Can be placed in space to extend existing space platforms.
descriptions.space-platform-starter-pack: Contains everything needed to set up a space platform foundation.
descriptions.metallic-asteroid-chunk: An asteroid chunk with high metal content.
descriptions.carbonic-asteroid-chunk: An asteroid chunk with high carbon content.
descriptions.oxide-asteroid-chunk: An asteroid chunk with high oxygen content.
descriptions.promethium-asteroid-chunk: An asteroid chunk only found when approaching the shattered planet.
descriptions.capture-robot-rocket: Grapples on and captures the targeted [entity=biter-spawner] into [entity=captive-biter-spawner].
descriptions.railgun-ammo: Used to break even the biggest asteroids.
descriptions.slowdown-capsule: Reduces the movement speed of affected enemies.
descriptions.belt-immunity-equipment: Prevents belts from moving the character.
descriptions.personal-roboport-equipment: Allows construction bots to work from your inventory.
descriptions.personal-roboport-mk2-equipment: Allows construction bots to work from your inventory.
descriptions.night-vision-equipment: Allows you to see more clearly in darkness.
descriptions.energy-shield-equipment: Provides an energy shield to protect the character.
descriptions.energy-shield-mk2-equipment: Provides an energy shield to protect the character.
descriptions.discharge-defense-equipment: Damages, pushes back and stuns nearby enemies when activated using the remote.
descriptions.land-mine: Explodes when enemies are nearby, damaging and stunning them.
descriptions.copper-wire: Used to manually connect and disconnect electric poles and power switches with Unknown control sequence: "build".
descriptions.green-wire: Used to connect machines to the circuit network using Unknown control sequence: "build".
descriptions.red-wire: Used to connect machines to the circuit network using Unknown control sequence: "build".
descriptions.artillery-targeting-remote: Allows firing artillery manually from the map or the world.
descriptions.item-unknown: This item is not available due to mod removal, it will be restored if the mod is re-enabled.

descriptions.quality-unknown: This quality is not available due to mod removal, it will be restored if the mod is re-enabled.

names.heavy-oil-cracking: Heavy oil cracking to light oil
names.light-oil-cracking: Light oil cracking to petroleum gas

descriptions.ammoniacal-solution-separation: [fluid=ammoniacal-solution] is gained by an [entity=offshore-pump] in the oceans of [planet=aquilo].
descriptions.recipe-unknown: This recipe is not available due to mod removal, it will be restored if the mod is re-enabled.

names.aquilo-solar-system-edge: Space route from [planet=aquilo]Aquilo to [space-location=solar-system-edge]Solar system edge
names.solar-system-edge-shattered-planet: Space route from [space-location=solar-system-edge]Solar system edge to [space-location=shattered-planet]Shattered planet

descriptions.nauvis: A temperate planet with shallow lakes and forests of woody trees. Rich in water, wood, iron, copper, coal, oil, and uranium. There are some hostile native species.
descriptions.vulcanus: A hot volcanic planet with mountainous volcanoes, rivers of lava, plains of ash, and sulfuric acid geysers. Rich in metals. Lava can only be crossed by elevated rail.
descriptions.gleba: A humid swampy planet with deep bogs, snaking hills, and fertile land. Rich in nutrients. Swamp terrain can be landfilled. Highground impedes railway but is needed for agriculture.
descriptions.fulgora:
A dry wind-swept planet with lightning storms on plateaus, and oceans of oil that can be bridged by elevated rails.
There appear to be some ruins.
descriptions.aquilo: A freezing wasteland with oceans of liquid ammonia and fluorine vents. Structures and belts will freeze if not heated by adjacent heat pipe or other hot structures.
descriptions.solar-system-edge: The end! Or rather, a new beginning. Building a space platform capable of surviving this far beyond the relative safety of the crash landing site proves your capability to travel anywhere else in the great depths of interstellar space beyond. For a space platform to survive this trip, it would need to be particularly self-sufficient and have the tools needed to turn the large, dangerous asteroids along the way into usable resources.
descriptions.shattered-planet: A mysterious remnant of a former world far in the depths of interstellar space. Its remnants, floating in the space it once occupied, hold the resources to unlock powerful technologies. However, accessing them is not without risk...

descriptions.advanced-asteroid-processing: Get a wider range of resources from asteroids.
descriptions.advanced-oil-processing: Crude oil refining with additional products that can be refined further.
descriptions.artificial-soil: Create soil for seeding more plants.
descriptions.artillery: Long range cannon mounted on a turret or train wagon. Used to automatically fire at distant enemy structures, or can be manually targeted at even longer distances.
descriptions.artillery-shell-range-1: Increases both the automatic and manual range of artillery.
descriptions.artillery-shell-speed-1: Increases the shooting speed of artillery.
descriptions.asteroid-reprocessing: Reprocess the impurities in asteroids to get a more suitable balance of resources.
descriptions.atomic-bomb: Devastating form of rockets used to eradicate anything in huge areas at a time.
descriptions.automated-rail-transportation: Enables building train stops and rail signals to set up automated train routes and coordinating multiple trains within the same rail network.
descriptions.automation: Key technology for automatic mass production.
descriptions.automation-2: Assembling machines capable of processing fluid ingredients.
descriptions.automation-3: Assembling machines capable of processing fluid ingredients, with additional speed and module slots.
descriptions.automation-science-pack: Allows research of basic automation methods.
descriptions.bacteria-cultivation: Multiply bacteria by feeding them some bioflux.
descriptions.battery: Electrochemical cell that stores and provides energy to electrical devices.
descriptions.battery-equipment: Inserted into armor to store excess energy for later.
descriptions.battery-mk2-equipment: Inserted into armor to store a lot of energy for later.
descriptions.belt-immunity-equipment: Inserted into armor to prevent you from being moved by transport belts.
descriptions.big-mining-drill: A larger more powerful mining drill with a wider mining area. Allows the mining of harder ores, such as the harder parts of tungsten deposits.
descriptions.bioflux: A combination of different plants could have a lot of uses.
descriptions.bioflux-processing: Using bioflux to get chemicals in a biological way.
descriptions.biolab: There appears to be a way to cultivate eggs into something...
descriptions.biter-egg-handling: Capturing a biter spawner and supplying it regular doses of [item=bioflux] allows biter eggs to be harvested, perhaps they could be made use of...
descriptions.braking-force-1: Trains can slow down faster, allowing them to stay at higher speeds longer.
descriptions.braking-force-2: Trains can slow down faster, allowing them to stay at higher speeds longer.
descriptions.braking-force-3: Trains can slow down faster, allowing them to stay at higher speeds longer.
descriptions.braking-force-4: Trains can slow down faster, allowing them to stay at higher speeds longer.
descriptions.braking-force-5: Trains can slow down faster, allowing them to stay at higher speeds longer.
descriptions.braking-force-6: Trains can slow down faster, allowing them to stay at higher speeds longer.
descriptions.braking-force-7: Trains can slow down faster, allowing them to stay at higher speeds longer.
descriptions.bulk-inserter: Inserters that can move multiple items of the same type at a time.
descriptions.calcite-processing: Use calcite to get steam, water, and heavy oil.
descriptions.captive-biter-spawner: Hatch eggs into captive spawners and place them anywhere on Nauvis.
descriptions.captivity: A robot capsule shot from a [item=rocket-launcher] injects a dose of [item=bioflux] into the spawner, capturing it. With regular doses of [item=bioflux], the spawner will remain captured.
descriptions.carbon-fiber: Some plants naturally grow carbon nanotubes, which can be spun into fiber, and woven into extremely strong cloth.
descriptions.chemical-science-pack: Allows research of advanced items, making use of oil products.
descriptions.circuit-network: Gives you better control over your machines by interconnecting them with wires and making them react to signals.
descriptions.cliff-explosives: Barrels filled with enough explosives to tear down cliffs.
descriptions.coal-liquefaction: A processing technique to turn coal into oil products with the use of steam and heavy oil.
descriptions.concrete: Advanced building material also used for flooring.
descriptions.construction-robotics: Construction robots can repair and build friendly entities. You can also order the robots to build new structures by placing a ghost there.
descriptions.cryogenic-plant: A crafting facility that can handle the extreme low temperatures needed for cryogenics.
descriptions.defender: Most basic type of combat robot. Follows and helps the player for a short time period.
descriptions.destroyer: Most advanced type of combat robot. Follows and helps the player for a limited time period.
descriptions.discharge-defense-equipment: Inserted into armor to damage, push back, and stun nearby enemies when activated using the remote.
descriptions.distractor: Intermediate type of combat robot. Stays on the deployed position to shoot and distract enemies.
descriptions.effect-transmission: The beacon transmits the effects of upgrade modules to nearby friendly entities. Transmission effects stack with diminishing returns.
descriptions.efficiency-module: A module that reduces the energy consumption of a machine.
descriptions.efficiency-module-2: A module that reduces the energy consumption of a machine.
descriptions.efficiency-module-3: A module that reduces the energy consumption of a machine.
descriptions.electric-energy-accumulators: Buildings that store excess electric energy for later.
descriptions.electric-energy-distribution-1: More flexible ways to distribute electricity.
descriptions.electric-energy-distribution-2: More flexible ways to distribute electricity.
descriptions.electric-weapons-damage-1: Increases the damage of electric beams.
descriptions.electric-weapons-damage-2: Increases the damage of electric beams.
descriptions.electric-weapons-damage-3: Increases the damage of electric beams.
descriptions.electric-weapons-damage-4: Increases the damage of electric beams.
descriptions.electromagnetic-plant: A crafting facility for more advanced use of magnets and electricity.
descriptions.electronics: Electronic components for basic signal processing.
descriptions.elevated-rail: Raised rail that can be placed over obstacles or water to reach new areas or make more efficient rail networks.
descriptions.energy-shield-equipment: Inserted into armor to absorb damage.
descriptions.energy-shield-mk2-equipment: Inserted into armor to absorb a large amount of damage.
descriptions.engine: Converts fuel into mechanical motion. An essential part of all vehicles.
descriptions.exoskeleton-equipment: Inserted into armor to increase movement speed. You can equip multiple exoskeletons at once.
descriptions.explosive-rocketry: Extremely explosive rockets with a larger explosion radius.
descriptions.fast-inserter: Inserters capable of faster motion and item filtering through improved electronics.
descriptions.fission-reactor-equipment: Inserted into armor to power other equipment.
descriptions.flamethrower: Powerful hand-held and turret flamethrowers firing aggressive liquids at enemies, setting them on fire.
descriptions.flammables: Developing more efficient fuel and more aggressive combustibles.
descriptions.fluid-handling: Various ways to store and transport fluids.
descriptions.fluid-wagon: Ability to transport fluids on rails. Fluid wagons are filled and emptied by pumps adjacent to straight rail segments.
descriptions.follower-robot-count-1: Increases the number of combat robots that can follow you at the same time.
descriptions.follower-robot-count-2: Increases the number of combat robots that can follow you at the same time.
descriptions.follower-robot-count-3: Increases the number of combat robots that can follow you at the same time.
descriptions.follower-robot-count-4: Increases the number of combat robots that can follow you at the same time.
descriptions.follower-robot-count-5: Increases the number of combat robots that can follow you at the same time.
descriptions.foundation: Engineered structural foundation with heat shielding and deep screw piles. Can be placed on lava, oil ocean, and most water.
descriptions.foundry: Allows more advanced smelting and other metallurgic advances.
descriptions.fusion-reactor: The dense plasma focus system allows us to create energy directly from the fusion reaction without the need to use steam engines.
descriptions.fusion-reactor-equipment: Inserted into armor to power other equipment.
descriptions.gate: Wall sections that open up when needed. Can be controlled by the circuit network.

descriptions.holmium-processing: Allows you to convert holmium ore to holmium plate.

descriptions.land-mine: Explosive traps built on the ground for enemies to walk over and trigger. Can be re-built by construction robots after exploding. Damage can be upgraded by researching stronger explosives.
descriptions.landfill: Can be placed on water to create terrain you can build on.

descriptions.logistic-robotics: Logistic robots can deliver items to the character, or take unwanted items away.
descriptions.logistic-science-pack: Allows research of improved logistics, automation, and simple military.
descriptions.logistic-system: Unlocks additional logistic chests which expands the capabilities of the logistic robots. Requester chests request items from the logistic network. Active provider chests push their contents to be stored or used elsewhere. Buffer chests request specified items to be available for personal logistics and automated construction.
descriptions.logistics: Faster and more flexible ways of transportation.
descriptions.logistics-2: Faster and more flexible ways of transportation.
descriptions.logistics-3: Faster and more flexible ways of transportation.
descriptions.low-density-structure: Light yet sturdy material, very useful for spaceships and personal equipment.
descriptions.lubricant: Converting heavy oils into lubricant, used to reduce friction in high-speed machines.
descriptions.metallurgic-science-pack: Allows study beyond the basics of metallurgy.
descriptions.military: More effective means to defend yourself and your factory.
descriptions.military-2: More effective means to defend yourself and your factory.
descriptions.military-3: More effective means to defend yourself and your factory.
descriptions.military-4: More effective means to defend yourself and your factory.

descriptions.mining-productivity-3: Increased yield from all mining drills and pumpjacks.
descriptions.modular-armor: Armor with a small grid for equipment modules that give you unique bonuses. Wearing it also increases your inventory size.
descriptions.modules: Allows you to research upgrade modules that can be inserted into machines.
descriptions.night-vision-equipment: Inserted into armor to allow you to see better at night.
descriptions.nuclear-fuel-reprocessing: The process of reprocessing used uranium fuel cells to create uranium-238.
descriptions.nuclear-power: Powerful and sophisticated method of power generation using uranium fuel cells.
descriptions.oil-processing: Crude oil refining used for manufacturing plastics, sulfur, and fuels.
descriptions.overgrowth-soil: More robust soil which allows growing plants anywhere in their biome.
descriptions.personal-laser-defense-equipment: Inserted into armor to automatically fire at nearby enemies.
descriptions.personal-roboport-equipment: Inserted into armor to allow construction robots to work from your inventory.
descriptions.personal-roboport-mk2-equipment: Inserted into armor to allow many construction robots to work from your inventory.

descriptions.planet-discovery-aquilo: A freezing wasteland with bottomless oceans of liquid ammonia that cannot be landfilled. Precarious icebergs are the closest thing to solid ground and can be extended with floating ice platform. Structures and belts will freeze if not heated by adjacent heat pipe or other hot structures, but must be placed on concrete to not melt the ice below.
descriptions.planet-discovery-fulgora:
A dry wind-swept planet with lightning storms on plateaus, and oceans of oil that can be bridged by elevated rails.
There appear to be some ruins.
descriptions.planet-discovery-gleba:
A humid swampy planet with nutrient-rich bogs. Wetland can support agriculture but is difficult to build on, it can be landfilled but stone is scarce.
Snaking hills have stone and are better to build on but can't support agriculture.
descriptions.planet-discovery-vulcanus: A hot volcanic planet with mountainous volcanoes, rivers of lava, plains of ash, and sulfuric acid geysers. Rich in metals. Lava can only be crossed by elevated rail.
descriptions.plastics: Synthetic polymeric materials that can be molded into solid objects.
descriptions.power-armor: Armor with a large equipment grid and inventory size bonus.
descriptions.power-armor-mk2: Armor with a huge equipment grid and inventory size bonus.
descriptions.production-science-pack: Allows research of more efficient machines and processes.
descriptions.productivity-module: A module that allows a machine to make more products from the same amount of ingredients, but it also increases energy consumption and reduces speed.

descriptions.rail-support-foundations: Allows to build elevated rails also on the deep parts of the oil ocean on [planet=fulgora].
descriptions.railgun: An electrically powered cross between a cannon and a sniper rifle.
descriptions.railgun-damage-1: Making railgun projectiles denser and sturdier results in more damage.
descriptions.railgun-shooting-speed-1: Improved cooling systems mean the railgun can shoot more often.
descriptions.recycling: The recycler reverses most processes except smelting and chemistry, returning 25% of the ingredients on average. Fluid ingredients are not regained. Other items are usually returned 25% of the time (losing 75%), or turned to spoilage if they were biological.

descriptions.tungsten-carbide: Allows you to make tungsten carbide, a hard heat resistant ceramic. Easily accessible tungsten ore can be found in some surface rocks of Vulcanus.
descriptions.tungsten-steel: Allows you to make tungsten-steel plate.
descriptions.uranium-ammo: Advanced ammunition from uranium-238 for higher hardness and weight, resulting in massive damage.
descriptions.uranium-mining: Allows you to use [fluid=sulfuric-acid] in [entity=electric-mining-drill] to mine [entity=uranium-ore]
descriptions.uranium-processing: Uranium ore is processed in centrifuges into uranium-238, with a chance to result in a richer uranium-235. Both are needed to create uranium fuel cells.

descriptions.spidertron: A versatile vehicle capable of traversing rough terrain. It's equipped with fast-firing rocket launchers controlled by manual or automatic targeting. Can be driven manually or using the spidertron remote.

descriptions.tile-unknown: This tile is not available due to mod removal, it will be restored if the mod is re-enabled.

descriptions.signal-everything:
If all input signals meet the condition, it will pass.
It is true when there are no inputs.
Output all input signals.
descriptions.signal-anything:
If any of the input signals meet the condition, it will pass.
It is false when there are no inputs.
Output the first input signal, or the first signal that passed all conditions, respecting signal order in both cases.
descriptions.signal-each:
Evaluates the condition for each input signal individually.
To pass completely, a signal has to pass all conditions.
Output every signal that passed all conditions.
descriptions.signal-item-parameter:
Special Wildcard signal
When used in schedule interrupt, it will match the first item that passes all wait conditions and replace the signal with that item.
This also replaces the rich text tag in the target stop name.
descriptions.signal-fuel-parameter:
Special Wildcard signal
When used in schedule interrupt, it will match the first fuel that passes all wait conditions and replace the signal with that fuel.
This also replaces the rich text tag in the target stop name.
descriptions.signal-fluid-parameter:
Special Wildcard signal
When used in schedule interrupt, it will match the first fluid that passes all wait conditions and replace the signal with that fluid.
This also replaces the rich text tag in the target stop name.
descriptions.signal-signal-parameter:
Special Wildcard signal
When used in schedule interrupt, it will match the first signal that passes all wait conditions and replace the signal with that signal.
This also replaces the rich text tag in the target stop name.
descriptions.signal-unknown: This signal is not available due to mod removal, it will be restored if the mod is re-enabled.
